cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, q-bio.GN, q-bio.TO 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network for predicting gene expression from histone modification data, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also proposes a novel optimization-based technique for visualizing the combinatorial interactions among histone modification marks, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of histone modifications in gene regulation, which is relevant to the sub-categories of computational biology (q-bio.GN) and genomics (q-bio.TO).
